Sports Business Ventures (SBV) is a sports brand and career development platform founded by Brian and Ellen Davison. With over 28 years of combined experience in the sports industry, SBV focuses on empowering aspiring and current sports professionals through various services, including media, community engagement, consulting, networking, mentorship, and recruitment.

Headquartered in the UK and US, SBV serves a community of over 100,000 members, providing access to job boards, newsletters, workshops, events, and educational courses. The company launched the first universal sports business club, emphasizing authentic relationships and career growth. Key offerings include a mentorship program that connects mentees with industry executives, consulting services for sports brands, and recruiting services in partnership with Careers Launch Talent Group. SBV is dedicated to shaping the future of the sports industry and fostering connections among professionals.

Arrow McLaren IndyCar Team is a professional racing team competing in the NTT IndyCar Series. Based in Indianapolis, Indiana, the team operates Chevrolet-powered Dallara chassis entries. It originated from Sam Schmidt Motorsports, founded in 2001, and has evolved through partnerships, with McLaren Racing holding a majority ownership since 2021.

The team has a rich history in IndyCar, debuting in 2001 and returning to full-time competition in 2011 as Schmidt Peterson Motorsports. It has secured multiple wins and podium finishes, with notable drivers like Pato O'Ward, Nolan Siegel, and Christian Lundgaard currently on the roster. Arrow McLaren has achieved significant milestones, including 27 overall wins and 87 podiums in its history. The team emphasizes innovation and growth, blending McLaren's Formula 1 expertise with its IndyCar operations.

Puffy is a direct-to-consumer e-commerce company based in North Hollywood, California, founded in 2016. The company specializes in premium sleep products designed to provide a comfortable and innovative sleeping experience. Puffy operates across the U.S. and Canada, focusing on customer satisfaction and high-quality manufacturing. All mattresses are assembled in the USA using CertiPUR-US certified foams, and the company offers free shipping within 1-2 days, a 101-night sleep trial, and lifetime warranties on its mattresses.

Puffy's product lineup includes a range of mattresses, such as the Puffy Original, Puffy Lux Hybrid, and Royal Hybrid, all featuring proprietary Cooling Cloud™ technology for breathability and comfort. In addition to mattresses, Puffy offers adjustable bed bases, bedding, pillows, weighted blankets, and sleep accessories aimed at enhancing sleep wellness. The company emphasizes a hassle-free customer experience with AI-powered support and a commitment to sleep health, making it a popular choice for consumers seeking quality sleep solutions.

Peterson Academy is an online education platform founded by Jordan Peterson, designed for intellectually ambitious learners around the globe. Launched in June 2019 and based in San Diego, CA, it offers affordable courses taught by professors from prestigious institutions like Harvard, Oxford, MIT, and Cambridge. The platform emphasizes intellectual autonomy and serious scholarship, providing over 600 hours of lectures and new courses added monthly.

Students can access high-quality content through a full annual subscription, which includes unlimited access to all current and future courses, community features, and mobile compatibility. Peterson Academy has enrolled over 50,000 students and fosters a vibrant intellectual community for discussion and discovery. The academy is committed to expanding its curriculum and offering multi-language support, aiming to redefine education by focusing on how to think rather than what to think.

Discogs is a web-based music database and online marketplace founded in October 2000 by Kevin Lewandowski in Portland, Oregon. Initially created to catalog a personal techno record collection, it has grown into the world's largest music database and trading platform for both physical and digital music formats. The platform serves a diverse community of music fans, collectors, DJs, and sellers, focusing on enhancing the collector's journey.

Discogs features a comprehensive, user-contributed catalog of millions of music releases across all genres, along with an online marketplace for buying, selling, and trading music items. Users can manage their personal music libraries with collection management tools and access the platform through mobile apps for iOS and Android. The company fosters a strong community through forums and volunteer-driven data collection, supporting its mission to connect music enthusiasts globally. Short Description:
The National Urban League (NUL) is a historic, nonpartisan civil rights organization founded in 1910 and based in New York City. It is dedicated to empowering African Americans and underserved communities through economic self-reliance, civil rights, and social justice. As the oldest and largest community-based movement of its kind in the United States, NUL operates with 90-100 local affiliates across 35 states and the District of Columbia, serving over 2-3.8 million people annually in more than 300 communities.

NUL focuses on five core pillars: workforce development, education, housing, health, and justice/civic engagement. It provides a range of services, including job placement and training, educational programs, entrepreneurship support, housing assistance, and health equity initiatives. The organization also engages in advocacy and research to promote racial equality and economic empowerment, generating a collective economic impact of $1.2 billion per year. Under the leadership of President Marc Morial, NUL continues its mission to remove barriers to racial equality and foster economic opportunities for all.

LlamaIndex is an open-source data framework and developer-first agent platform based in San Francisco, CA. Founded in 2022, it connects large language models (LLMs) with external data sources to create retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) applications and AI workflows. The platform has gained significant traction, with over 4 million monthly package downloads and more than 200,000 users on LlamaCloud.

The company offers a comprehensive ecosystem for LLM applications, including an open-source framework with tools for data ingestion, structuring, and querying. LlamaCloud provides a cloud-based platform for document automation, while LlamaParse is an API for transforming unstructured data into RAG-ready formats. LlamaIndex also features a modular agent framework for context-aware automation, collaborating with Nvidia on blueprints for research and writing agents. The company serves major enterprises like Rakuten Group, The Carlyle Group, and Salesforce, supporting complex RAG pipelines and AI assistants.

Short Description:
Phantom is a multi-chain cryptocurrency wallet and web3 platform based in San Francisco, California. Founded in 2021, it allows users to buy, trade, store, and manage digital assets with a strong emphasis on self-custody and security. The platform is designed for ease of use, requiring no personal information for access, and enables users to maintain full control of their funds.

Phantom supports multiple blockchain networks within a single wallet, allowing for unlimited token storage and real-time activity monitoring. It features seamless integration with major NFT marketplaces, providing tools for managing NFT collections. Users can also perform fast token swaps and engage in token staking to earn rewards. Additionally, Phantom offers in-wallet perpetual futures trading, enhancing its trading capabilities with advanced features like risk management tools and leverage options.

The platform prioritizes security with multiple layers, including scam detection and hardware wallet compatibility. Phantom caters to a diverse audience, including retail investors, traders, and NFT collectors, and has formed partnerships with key players in the ecosystem.

Short Description:
The New York Foundation for the Arts (NYFA) is a nonprofit organization established in 1971 in New York City. It provides resources, guidance, and funding to individual artists and emerging arts organizations. NYFA aims to empower artists across various creative disciplines, focusing on diversity, equity, inclusion, and accessibility. The organization serves approximately 1 million constituents annually through both in-person and virtual initiatives.

NYFA operates four main programs that include grants, training, and sponsorship. It awards between $2 million and $55 million each year through its Artists' Fellowships, supporting nearly 1,000 artists primarily in New York State. The foundation also offers fiscal sponsorship, helping artists and arts organizations manage funding for their projects. Additionally, NYFA provides professional development opportunities, online resources, and advocacy for arts funding and freedom of expression. The organization is committed to addressing systemic marginalization and supports artists nationwide and globally.

Short Description:
TalentAlly is a diversity-focused job board and recruitment platform that connects job seekers from diverse backgrounds with inclusive employers. Originally known as Professional Diversity Network, the company rebranded to reflect its mission of serving all talented individuals. Headquartered in Chicago, Illinois, TalentAlly has approximately 350 employees and was founded in 1999.

The platform offers a range of services for job seekers, including access to job listings, AI-powered virtual interview practice, resume optimization tools, and professional development resources. TalentAlly also hosts over 40 national career fairs annually. For employers, the platform provides job posting services, branded employer profiles, and AI-driven recruitment tools to enhance candidate engagement and streamline the hiring process. With a commitment to bridging the gap between diverse individuals and inclusive companies, TalentAlly aims to facilitate 1 million job placements by 2026.

Short Description:
Haus Labs by Lady Gaga is a clean, cruelty-free, and vegan cosmetics brand founded in September 2019. Initially launched as Haus Laboratories, the brand focuses on high-performance makeup that combines artistry, skincare benefits, and sustainability. It was the first major beauty line to launch exclusively on Amazon and quickly gained recognition, achieving third place among celebrity makeup brands in 2020.

In June 2022, the brand underwent a strategic rebrand to Haus Labs by Lady Gaga and formed an exclusive partnership with Sephora, expanding its reach to North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, the UK, and Canada by 2023. Haus Labs emphasizes clean beauty by reformulating products to eliminate over 2,600 potentially harmful ingredients. The brand specializes in color cosmetics, featuring innovative products like the Trilocone Skin Tech Foundation, which is available in 51 shades and clinically shown to enhance skin health. With a commitment to sustainability and ingredient-conscious beauty, Haus Labs continues to grow and innovate in the cosmetics industry.

The Cybersecurity Marketing Society is a professional community founded in 2020 by Gianna Whitver and Maria Velasquez, based in New York City. It supports cybersecurity marketers by providing resources, networking opportunities, education, and advocacy. Initially starting as a Slack channel, the organization has grown into a national community that addresses the unique challenges of marketing within the cybersecurity sector.

The society offers various services, including networking through Slack channels, meetups, and peer support. It hosts events like the Cyber Marketing Con, webinars, and workshops to enhance skills and foster connections. Members benefit from expert-led resources, personalized career support, and a job board for career advancement. The society also produces industry research and hosts a podcast titled "Breaking Through in Cybersecurity Marketing," focusing on discussions relevant to the field.

Short Description:
Vacation Inc. is a Miami-based skincare brand founded in 2021, focusing on sunscreens, scents, and lotions that combine UV protection with nostalgic fragrances inspired by beach holidays. The company aims to be "the world's best-smelling sunscreen," appealing to consumers who value both sun safety and sensory enjoyment. Products are developed in collaboration with dermatologist Dr. Elizabeth Hale and renowned perfumers Carlos Huber and Rodrigo Flores-Roux.

The brand emphasizes a retro, 1980s-inspired aesthetic and has experienced significant growth, including a 200% increase in sales in 2023 and a $6 million Series A funding round in May 2023. Vacation Inc. has expanded its presence to over 1,200 Ulta Beauty and Target locations, earning recognition as an innovative player in the sun-care market. Their product range includes various sunscreen formulations, perfumes, body mists, and lotions, all designed with high-quality, environmentally conscious ingredients. The packaging features eye-catching retro designs, enhancing the overall leisure experience.

Short Description:
Centurion encompasses several distinct companies operating in various sectors. Centurion Energy & Industrial Services is a global leader in equipment rentals and project management, serving critical industries such as energy and construction across 12 countries. The Centurion US Region focuses on providing production services and equipment rentals specifically for the US energy sector.

Centurion Service Group specializes in surplus medical equipment auctions and lifecycle services, connecting hospitals and buyers worldwide. The Centurion Group offers professional security and investigation services, leveraging over 125 years of combined law enforcement experience. Lastly, Centurion Health delivers comprehensive medical, dental, and behavioral health services to correctional facilities across multiple states. Each entity operates independently, catering to its specific market and customer needs.

Short Description:
Anatomage Inc. is a leader in medical virtualization technology, founded in 2004 by Dr. Jack Choi. The company specializes in 3D anatomy hardware, software, and visualization tools designed for healthcare education, diagnosis, treatment planning, and clinical applications. Headquartered in Santa Clara, California, Anatomage employs between 51 and 200 people and generates approximately $26.1 million in annual revenue.

Anatomage offers a range of innovative products, including the Anatomage Table, a life-size virtual dissection table that provides real-human-based visualization from digitized cadavers. Their Invivo5 software is an award-winning radiology tool used in conjunction with leading radiology equipment. The company also provides image-guided surgical devices, educational display equipment, and cloud-based solutions. With a presence in over 20 countries, Anatomage's products are utilized in tens of thousands of clinics and hospitals worldwide, enhancing the quality of medical education and healthcare delivery.

Betches Media is a multimedia entertainment brand founded by Aleen Dreksler, Jordana Abraham, and Samantha Sage in 2011. Originally a satirical blog, it has grown into a multi-platform company that connects with millennial and Gen Z women through humor and empowerment. Betches has reached 43 million monthly users and boasts a significant social media presence, including 13 million Instagram followers and 40 million podcast downloads.

The company offers a variety of content across digital platforms, podcasts, newsletters, events, and merchandise. Its digital content includes a website with verticals on news, entertainment, relationships, and lifestyle, along with engaging videos on TikTok and YouTube. Betches produces popular podcasts like *The Betchelor* and hosts live events such as the Betches Who Brunch Comedy Tour. Additionally, it sells branded merchandise and creates opportunities for creators within its ecosystem. In 2023, Betches was acquired by LBG Media to support its global expansion as a leading humor brand for women.

Recognized as the "Official Shoe of Cheerleading®," the company has pioneered items such as the first spring floor-specific shoe and cheer-specific backpacks. Nfinity also hosts events like The Finals and the Nfinity Cup, and it supports athletes through initiatives like the GenNEXT program and "The Legends" recognition for elite performers.

Short Description:
LiveKit is an open-source platform and cloud service designed for building real-time voice, video, and AI-powered applications using WebRTC technology. It simplifies the complexities of WebRTC infrastructure, offering both self-hosted and fully-managed cloud deployment options. Key components include a Selective Forwarding Unit (SFU) for efficient media routing, a LiveKit Server for managing sessions, and Client SDKs for various programming languages.

The platform features secure connection management, media recording and streaming capabilities, and AI-native functionalities such as voice recognition and real-time transcription. LiveKit supports a variety of use cases, including telehealth applications, virtual classrooms, interactive live events, and multiplayer games. With over 20,000 developers and teams utilizing its services, LiveKit has established itself as a valuable resource for businesses ranging from freelancers to large enterprises. Notable users include OpenAI and Podium, showcasing its versatility in powering innovative communication solutions.

Short Description:
Black Hat is a well-known series of cybersecurity conferences and events that began in 1997, founded by Jeff Moss. It focuses on technical information security research, presentations, and training. Black Hat serves as a platform for idea exchange between hackers and software companies, offering a unique environment that fosters creativity and collaboration. The event has gained recognition for its bold discussions on topics such as cyberwarfare, cryptography, and OS vulnerabilities.

The offerings at Black Hat include high-level technical briefings, hands-on training courses, and keynote panels. Notable training courses include "The Shellcode Lab" and "Practical Threat Intelligence." The events feature presentations from industry experts, showcasing the latest in hacking techniques, reverse engineering tools, and emerging trends in cybersecurity. Black Hat hosts global editions, including Black Hat USA and Asia, and is often referred to as "cybersecurity summer camp" or "hacker boot camp."
